      {
        "id": "6e1db462-e154-4eb0-b0e8-d69c544ad22e",
        "score": 0.65180576,
        "text": "The document is an appendix from the \"2022 State of the Market Report\" focusing on the monthly aggregate costs of various ERCOT market settlement totals for 2022. It includes a table titled \"Table A2: Market at a Glance Monthly,\" which details costs in millions of dollars across different categories for each month.\n\nKey categories include:\n\n- **Energy**: Costs range from $1,053 million in January to $2,321 million in December, with a peak of $7,561 million in July.\n- **Regulation Up/Down**: Costs vary monthly, with notable peaks in July for Regulation Up ($18 million) and consistent low values for Regulation Down.\n- **Responsive Reserve**: Peaks at $91 million in July, with lower values in other months.\n- **Non-Spin**: Highest in July at $141 million.\n- **CRR Auction Distribution**: Ranges from $65 million in February to $114 million in June.\n- **Balancing Account Surplus**: Peaks at $72 million in June.\n- **CRR DAM Payment**: Highest in May at $430 million.\n- **PTP DAM/RT Payment**: Notable peaks in May ($390 million) and June ($574 million) respectively.\n- **Emergency Response Service**: Generally low, with a peak of $6 million in January.\n- **Revenue Neutrality Uplift**: Fluctuates, with negative values in March and July.\n- **AS Imbalance Uplift**: Peaks in April at $13 million, with negative values in July.\n- **ERCOT Fee**: Consistent around $17-$26 million monthly.\n- **ERO Passthrough Fee**: Steady at $2 million monthly.\n- **Firm Fuel**: Only appears in November and December.\n- **Other Load Allocation**: Minor fluctuations, with some negative values.\n\nOverall, the table provides a comprehensive monthly breakdown of costs associated with various market activities within ERCOT for 2022.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/ERCOT/report/2022/page_156.jpg",
          "page_num": 156,
          "title": "State of the Market Report for the ERCOT Electricity Markets",
          "year": 2022,
          "market": "ERCOT",
          "data_type": "report"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "568ace02-e59f-49e1-aee3-5616a215f358",
        "score": 0.6473745,
        "text": "The document provides an analysis of the 2023 prices and outcomes in ERCOT's real-time energy market. It includes a table (Table A1) summarizing the annual aggregate costs of various ERCOT charges or payments, including ancillary services. The table lists different cost types and their annual totals in millions of dollars. Key figures include:\n\n- Energy costs: $28,965 million\n- Regulation Up: $119 million\n- Regulation Down: $48 million\n- Responsive Reserve: $407 million\n- Non-Spin: $426 million\n- ECRS: $669 million\n- CRR DAM Payment: $1,807 million\n- PTP DAM Charge: $1,613 million\n- PTP RT Payment: $1,836 million\n- Net Cost of Electricity: $35,161 million\n\nThe document notes that these figures reflect net charges after self-arrangement and are based on real-time energy values rather than settlement data. Table A2, not shown, presents monthly aggregate costs for 2023.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/ERCOT/report/2023/page_161.jpg",
          "page_num": 161,
          "title": "State of the Market Report for the ERCOT Electricity Markets",
          "year": 2023,
          "market": "ERCOT",
          "data_type": "report"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "7874e0da-69a6-4e61-9e77-e476b4f80095",
        "score": 0.64580905,
        "text": "The document provides an analysis of 2021 prices and outcomes in ERCOT's real-time energy market. It includes a table (Table A1) summarizing the annual aggregate costs of various ERCOT charges or payments for 2021, categorized by cost type. The major costs listed are:\n\n- Energy: $65,946 million\n- Regulation Up: $869 million\n- Regulation Down: $348 million\n- Responsive Reserve: $8,232 million\n- Non-Spin: $2,176 million\n- CRR Auction Distribution: $831 million\n- Balancing Account Surplus: $111 million\n- CRR DAM Payment: $1,289 million\n- PTP DAM Charge: $1,113 million\n- PTP RT Payment: $1,563 million\n- Emergency Response Service: $59 million\n- Revenue Neutrality: $1 million\n- ERCOT Fee: $218 million\n- Other Load Allocation: $1,831 million\n\nThe section also discusses real-time market prices, noting that they vary significantly by time of day. It mentions that Figure A1 (not shown) illustrates the load-weighted average real-time prices for peak and off-peak categories for each month in 2021. Peak hours are defined as hour ending (HE) 7 to HE 22 on weekdays, while off-peak includes all other hours. These categories align with those traded in forward markets.",
        "metadata": {
          "drive_path": "gs://tumeai-rag/ERCOT/report/2021/page_157.jpg",
          "page_num": 157,
          "title": "State of the Market Report for the ERCOT Electricity Markets",
          "year": 2021,
          "market": "ERCOT",
          "data_type": "report"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "4eb89e8e-5866-45e6-87d2-1b7f77822851",
        "score": 0.6385498,
        "text": "This document page is an appendix section titled \"Statistics at a Glance\" from the 2024 State of the Market Report. It provides supplemental analysis related to the 2024 prices and outcomes in ERCOT\u2019s real-time energy market. The appendix explains that it presents methods and motivations for the analyses, while the main report discusses conclusions and recommendations for market design and competitiveness.\n\nThe key content includes a table (Table A1) summarizing the annual aggregate costs and payments in millions of dollars for various ERCOT charges or payments in 2024. These include ancillary service charges by type and other fees or surpluses. The table highlights:\n\n- Energy costs totaling $14,472 million\n- Regulation Up and Down charges of $26 million and $14 million respectively\n- Responsive Reserve at $109 million\n- Non-Spin at $161 million\n- ECRS at $147 million\n- CRR Auction Distribution showing a negative value of ($1,710) million\n- Balancing Account Surplus of $239 million\n- Emergency Response Service at $73 million\n- Revenue Neutrality Uplift at $161 million\n- AS Imbalance Uplift showing a negative value of ($8) million\n- ERCOT Admin Fee at $292 million\n- ERO Passthrough Fee at $28 million\n- Firm Fuel Supply Service at $38 million\n- Other Load Allocation at $9 million\n\nThe net cost of electricity after these adjustments is $13,999 million.\n\nThe appendix notes that the energy value is calculated based on megawatts generated rather than settlement data, and that the costs shown do not reflect the total cost of each ancillary service but only net charges after self-arrangement. The appendix serves to provide a detailed financial snapshot of ERCOT\u2019s real-time market for 2024.",
