        "text": "The document discusses the 2018 electricity market outcomes, focusing on costs associated with operating reserves and reliability. The highest monthly average operating reserve adder was $7.19 per MWh in July, and the highest reliability adder was $0.54 per MWh in May. Ancillary services costs increased to $1.60 per MWh from $0.87 in 2017.\n\nUplift costs rose to $1.08 per MWh in 2018, up from $1.02 in 2017, totaling approximately $408 million. Major components of uplift costs include the ERCOT system administrative fee ($209 million) and ERS program costs ($50 million). The revenue neutrality allocation (RENA) increased by almost 40%, from $96 million in 2017 to $134 million in 2018. Figure 2 provides an analysis of uplift and RENA for 2018.",
