        "text": "The document discusses proposed revisions to the ERCOT Protocols initiated in 2017, focusing on the Mitigated Offer Cap for Reliability Must-Run (RMR) resources. Key points include:\n\n1. **RMR Resource Dispatch**: The proposal allows RMR resources to be dispatched but priced above other resources solving the same constraint.\n\n2. **Operations and Maintenance (O&M) Costs**: Updates to O&M costs must be submitted to ERCOT every three months, aligning with the schedule for updated RMR budgets. The proposal also requires submissions to include all variable costs for up to a ten-year historical period.\n\n3. **Third-Party Evaluation**: A proposal allows third-party evaluation of budget items and adjustments to standby payments as cost information changes.\n\n4. **Final Reconciliation**: Ensures RMR payments are accurate, requiring ERCOT to issue a miscellaneous invoice to reconcile final RMR costs within 30 days after the Real-Time Market True-Up Statement is issued for the RMR agreement termination date.\n\nThese revisions aim to improve the accuracy and transparency of RMR cost management.",
