        "text": "The document discusses revenue sufficiency related to transmission congestion and CRRs (Congestion Revenue Rights). It compares payments to Point-to-Point (PTP) obligation owners and other day-ahead positions against real-time congestion rent for 2016 and 2017.\n\n- In 2017, real-time congestion rent was $967 million. Payments for PTP obligations (including CRR options) were $812 million, and payments for other day-ahead positions were $251 million, resulting in a shortfall of approximately $96 million.\n\n- In 2016, real-time congestion rent was $497 million. Payments for PTP obligations and real-time CRRs were $437 million, and payments for other day-ahead positions were $88 million, resulting in a shortfall of approximately $28 million.\n\nThe shortfall is covered by charges to load. The accompanying graph (Figure 57) illustrates the monthly real-time congestion rent and payments for 2016 and 2017.",
